article.headline: Chicago St. 82, W. Illinois 72
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- David Holston scored 34 points to lead Chicago State to an 82-72 win over Western Illinois on Saturday. The Cougars (8-15,) shot 53.7 percent from the field. Holston led the way, converting 11-of-18 field goals, including 7-of-12 from beyond the the three-point arc. Chicago State never trailed in the game, but led by just five at halftime. The Cougars converted 6-of-7 3-pointers in the second half to pull away, and led by as many as 15 with 10:27 remaining. Royce Parran scored 13 points for Chicago State. Kourtney Calvin added 11 points and a game-high 13 rebounds. David Jackson scored 21 points to lead the Leathernecks (4-16).
